Package: CohortIntelligence
Title: OHDSI-Native Cohort Exploration and Hypothesis Generation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Minqi", "Xiong",
           email = "mxiong5@jhu.edu",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: A data-driven workbench that sits between aggregate cohort
    diagnostics and formal downstream analysis for OMOP CDM studies. Helps
    researchers identify which cohort patterns, subgroups, and patients deserve
    targeted clinical or methodological review before committing to a formal
    study design. Accepts cohorts defined by ATLAS JSON files (via 'CirceR') or
    pre-instantiated cohort tables. Key capabilities: (1) reactive quilt plot
    -- patient x domain x time-window heatmap for a bird's-eye cohort view;
    (2) unsupervised ML pipeline -- UMAP ('uwot'), clustering ('cluster'), and
    isolation-forest anomaly scoring ('isotree') to detect subgroups and
    out-of-distribution patients; (3) signal explanation -- per-patient
    priority explanation cards; (4) cluster profile summaries -- cautious
    descriptive labels and prevalence comparisons per cluster; (5) review sets
    -- eight guided patient groups to structure cohort inspection, clinician
    discussion, and targeted chart-review planning; (6) temporal rule flags --
    rule-based detection of structured-data patterns that warrant review;
    (7) clinician meeting report export -- self-contained HTML packet covering
    cohort landscape, cluster profiles, review sets, temporal flags, and
    candidate hypotheses. All outputs are hypothesis-generating and require
    clinical validation; this tool does NOT replace CohortDiagnostics, ATLAS,
    or formal chart review or clinical adjudication. Designed for OMOP CDM
    v5.3/5.4. ML packages required:
    install.packages(c('uwot', 'cluster', 'isotree')).
